Low-energy effective action and background of 2D string theory 


Now we turn to the string theory side of the problem.
In a general background the string theory is defined by the following
-model action

metr:smod 
S_14 d^2 h 
[G_ (X)h^ab _a X^  _b X^ 
+(X) + T(X)],

where  is a two-dimensional field on the world sheet.
As it is well known the condition that the conformal invariance of
this theory is unbroken reduces to some equations on
the background fields: target space metric ,
dilaton  and tachyon .
These equations can be obtained from the effective action which in
the leading order in  is given bymetr:Seff 
S_eff =d^2 X  -G e^-2  [ 16 +
R+4()^2-(T)^2+4 T^2].
Here the covariant derivative
