^T &=&-2^2 T +4 T-8 T=0. Let us concentrate on the tachyonic part of the action metr:Seff .
We want to relate it to the action metr:Sg  for the collective theory obtained
form Matrix Quantum Mechanics. In particular, the tachyon field
 and quantum fluctuation of density 
should be correctly identified with each other.
We see that the main difference between metr:Seff 
and metr:Sg  is the presence of the dilaton dependent factor .
To remove this factor, we redefine the tachyon as .
Then the part of the action quadratic in the tachyon field reads
metr:Stach 
