Structure of the target space 


In this subsection we investigate the concrete form of the target
space which is obtained as the image under the coordinate
transformation trivializing the metric. From the previous subsection
it follows that this transformation is a superposition of the map
metr:flcor  and a conformal change of coordinates
metr:confch .  Since the latter remains unknown, we will analyze
only the image of the map metr:flcor .  It will be sufficient to
get a general picture because conformal transformations do not change
the causal structure of spacetime.

We restrict our analysis to the case of the simplest non-trivial
perturbation with  in metr:SLbac .  It corresponds to the
conformal Sine-Liouville theory. At  this theory is T-dual to
the CFT suggested to describe string theory on the black hole
background.  We also assume that the coefficients
 in metr:SLbac  are positive what corresponds to the
positivity of the coupling constants .
It is the case which was considered in
.

To find the image, we investigate the change of coordinates at infinity
of the  plane which plays the role of the boundary of the initial
spacetime. In other words, we want to find where the boundary is mapped to.
Thus we assume  and  to be large and look at the dependence
of  of their ratio. At the asymptotics  can be easily
found, but the answer depends non-continuously on  as well as on the
parameter .
There are several different cases which we summarize in Appendix C.

